    "body": "i added a test package here https://github.com/dgoncharov/bitcoin/tree/test_package.\r\nIf you checkout this branch, you can see the value of MAKEFLAGS, that make passes to its children.\r\nE.g.\r\n\r\n\r\n```\r\n$ TEST=1 make test_configured -k -j2 --no-print-directory \r\nExtracting test...\r\nPreprocessing test...\r\nConfiguring test...\r\nin print_makeflags.mk MAKEFLAGS=k --no-print-directory\r\nin print_makeflags.mk in the recipe MAKEFLAGS=k -j2 --jobserver-auth=4,5 --no-print-directory\r\nmake[1]: 'all' is up to date.\r\n$\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou can then pass various flags and see the output.\r\nOr whatever other test you want to run.\r\nThere is simply too many combinations to list them in the makefile itself.",
